<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Configure EC2 instances</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 2 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>To prepare the EC2 instances that will host the master and worker nodes before you install CDF and the suite, the following tasks must be completed.
</p>
<ol>
<li>Run the following command to check if the required rpm packages have been installed on all nodes.
<pre>rpm -qa | grep -E "java-1.8.0-openjdk|libgcrypt|libseccomp|libtool-ltdl|net-tools|nfs-utils|systemd-libs|device-mapper-libs|lsof|unzip|chrony|rpcbind|httpd-tools|conntrack"</pre>
<p>If one or more packages are missing install them using yum install.
</p>
<pre>yum install java-1.8.0-openjdk libgcrypt libseccomp libtool-ltdl net-tools nfs-utils systemd-libs device-mapper-libs lsof unzip chrony rpcbind httpd-tools conntrack -y</pre></li>
<li>Configure thin pool devices on all nodes by running the following commands:
<pre>yum install lvm2
pvcreate /dev/xvdb
vgcreate docker /dev/xvdb
lvcreate --wipesignatures y -n thinpool docker -l 95%VG
lvcreate --wipesignatures y -n thinpoolmeta docker -l 1%VG
lvconvert -y --zero n -c 512K --thinpool docker/thinpool --poolmetadata docker/thinpoolmeta
vi /etc/lvm/profile/docker_thinpool.profile
activation {
thin_pool_autoextend_threshold=80
thin_pool_autoextend_percent=20
}
chmod 760 /etc/lvm/profile/docker_thinpool.profile
lvchange --metadataprofile docker_thinpool docker/thinpool
lvs -o+seg_monitor
pvcreate /dev/xvdc
vgcreate docker_bootstrap /dev/xvdc
lvcreate --wipesignatures y -n bootstrap_thinpool docker_bootstrap -l 95%VG
lvcreate --wipesignatures y -n bootstrap_thinpoolmeta docker_bootstrap -l 1%VG
lvconvert -y --zero n -c 512K --thinpool docker_bootstrap/bootstrap_thinpool --poolmetadata docker_bootstrap/bootstrap_thinpoolmeta
vi /etc/lvm/profile/docker_bootstrap.profile
activation {
thin_pool_autoextend_threshold=80
thin_pool_autoextend_percent=20
}
chmod 760 /etc/lvm/profile/docker_bootstrap.profile
lvchange --metadataprofile docker_bootstrap docker_bootstrap/bootstrap_thinpool
lvs -o+seg_monitor</pre></li></ol>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Set_the_system_parameters">Set the system parameters</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/CoECInOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Set the system parameters">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/CoECInOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Set the system parameters">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table>
